column4: Sampling time in local time (local time is UTC-3)
Concentration of total suspended solids reported in milligrams per liter (mg/L) and determined in samples filtered using Whatman GF/C 47mm circles
Concentration of inorganic suspended solids reported in milligrams per liter (mg/L) and determined by ignition of volatile suspended solids at 480 deg. Celsius

Concentration of organic suspended solids concentration reported in milligrams per liter (mg/L) and calculated as the difference between measured total suspended solids and inorganic suspended solids.
Chlorophyll-a concentration reported  in micograms per liter (ug/L) and determined spectrophotometrically; samples filtered using Whatman GF/F 47mm circles
Dissolved inorganic carbon concentration reported in milligrams per liter (mg/L) and determined using a Shimadzu TOC 5000A carbon analyzer calibrated with potassium biphthalate
Dissolved organic carbon reported in milligrams per liter (mg/L) and determined using a Shimadzu TOC 5000A carbon analyzer calibrated with potassium biphthalate
Transparency  reported as Secchi depth in meters (m) and measured using a 20 cm diameter Secchi disk
Turbidity reported in nephelometric turbidity units (NTU) and measured using Horiba U-10
Temperature reported in degrees Celsius and measured using Horiba U-10
Conductivity reported in millisiemens per centimeter (mS/cm) and measured using Horiba U-10

Carbon dioxide concentration reported in micromoles of carbon dioxide per liter (umol CO2/L) calculated from pH, dissolved inorganic carbon, temperature, and conductivity as described in Rudorff et al. (2011)

column2: In September 2003 water was collected with a cylindrical sampler which integrated the water column from surface to the Secchi depth.
